iscussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"During an async request no other sync and async calls are allowed,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and will result in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pending"},{"text":" errors.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"type":"text","text":" larger than "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_MAXSSIZE"},{"text":" will cause a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"invalidArgument"},{"text":" error.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On success, the number of bytes skipped will be passed to the callback.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is not an error if this is not the same as the requested size, as it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can happen e.g. near the end of a file, but generally we try to skip"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as many bytes as requested. Zero is returned on end of file"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(or if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"type":"text","text":" is zero), but never otherwise."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Any outstanding i\/o request with higher priority (lower numerical value)","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will be executed before an outstanding request with lower priority.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Default priority is [PRIORITY_DEFAULT](\/\/documentation\/glib\/priority_default."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The asynchronous methods have a default fallback that uses threads to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implement asynchronicity, so they are optional for inheriting classes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"However, if you override one, you mus